A Nyeri man accused of murdering his mother and seriously injuring his father has been remanded for 14 days for further investigations. Boniface Maina, 30, allegedly stabbed his mother in the stomach with a kitchen knife two times and attacked his father in Mbiriri village, Kieni East, on Tuesday. Maina's father is admitted at Tumutumu Hospital in critical condition.The motive has not been established. The case will be mentioned on February 8.